<TITLE> Garment workers strike for better conditions </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Gazipur, April 10 (bdnews24.com)  Workers in two garments factories in Gazipur came out on strike on Saturday. Sayed Md. Azharul Islam, sub-inspector of Konabari police camp told journalists that the workers of YK Knitwear stopped working in the morning as the wages for making sweaters was reduced from Tk 35 to Tk 32. The angry workers beat up three factory officials and the situation only came under control with positive intervention from the police, he said. Md. Anwar Hossain of Joydevpur police station said that the workers of Spero garments factory started to demonstrate demanding their wage arrears, and holidays on the Bangla New Year and week ends. They stopped working at around 2 pm and at one stage they blocked Dhaka-Gaazipur highway for 15 minutes, said Hossain. Police moved the angry workers from the highway and, with promises from the factory officials to pay the arrears on Sunday, they returned to work at around 3 pm, he added. bdnews2
